div.p:
For thine is the &c.] We haue been bold to beg all these things of thee (oh holy Father▪) because all kingdome, power & glorie are onelie thine; acknowledging
that we haue receiued all from thy heauenly bounty; and being assured th thou wilt grāt vs all these things for thy Sonnes sake, and whatsoeuer else is good for vs, so far as shall bee for thine owne glorie, seeing thou art absolute Lord & King in heauē and in earth, and doest dispose, guide and ouerrule all things, as shal make most for thine owne glorie, and the greatest good of vs thine obedient
subiects and children;
